\begin_layout Standard
\paragraph_spacing onehalf
Suppose we have two countries (home, 
\begin_inset Formula $h$
\end_inset

 and foreign, 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

).
 For simplicity we assume that the 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{t}^{h}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{t}^{f}$
\end_inset

 are conditionally independent.
 The exchange rate is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
e_{t}^{h,f} & = & \frac{\Pi_{t}^{h}}{\Pi_{t}^{f}}\\
\\
e_{t}^{h,f} & = & exp\left(\int_{0}^{t}\left((r_{s}^{N,h}-r_{s}^{N,f})-(r_{s}^{R,h}-r_{s}^{R,f})\right)ds\right)\\
